01/04/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Miroslav Lajcak said on Monday (March 31st) that the international community will continue to support the exhumation and identification of those killed during the 1990s conflicts in BiH. Speaking on the 5th anniversary of a ceremony to bury victims of the 1995 Srebrenica massacre, Lajcak said that without justice there can be no reconciliation. Since those first 600 victims were buried on March 31st 2003, 2,907 more victims have been buried. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 01/04/08; RTRS, NTV Hayat, OHR website - 31/03/08) 
